very of health education services.</p><p>Provides direct group or one-to-one health education services to clients, caregivers and the</p><p>public using IAH/SCAN approved content, guidelines and materials.</p><p>Prepares reports, grants, proposals, and documentation, as assigned.</p><p>Adheres to all quality, compliance and regulatory standards to achieve IAH and SCAN</p><p>outcomes.</p><p>JOB DESCRIPTION</p><p>Actively supports the achievement of SCAN and IAHâs Vision and Goals.</p><p>Maintains professional and technical knowledge by attending educational workshops;</p><p>reviewing and contributing to professional publications; establishing personal networks;</p><p>participating in professional societies.</p><p>Contributes to team effort by accomplishing related results as needed.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>PREFERRED QUALIFICATIONS: Bachelorâs Degree required. Masterâs Degree in public health or Registered Nurse preferred. MCHES (Master Certified Health Education Specialist) or CHES (Certified Health Education Specialist) certification strongly preferred. Experience managing data from surveys Experience with Survey Software Experience developing, writing, editing and evaluating health education materials 2+ years of experience in health education. Proficiency in a second language preferred. Demonstrated experience managing multiple projects. Demonstrated public speaking skills. Strong interpersonal skills, including excellent written and communication skills. Knowledge of and experience with social services, caregivers and older adult populations. Proficiency in Microsoft Office. CONDITIONS OF WORK: Office Hours: Monday â Friday 8am to 5pm. Extended work hours as needed. Maintain valid driverâs license, automobile insurance and reliable transportation. Heavy phone and computer usage Regular travel throughout Los Angeles County and surrounding areas. While this job description is intended to be an accurate reflection of the essential job results, man